          "explanation": "Ans. is 'a' i.e., Topical coicosteroids Treatment of Lichen planus The first line treatment of lichen planus are topical coicosteroids. Second choice would be systemic coicosteroids for symptom control and possibly more rapid resolution. Oral antihistaminics are given for pruritic. PUVA can be used for extensive lesions. Acitretin can be used for mucosal lesions."
