          "explanation": "Ans: a (Atopic dermatitis)Ref: Rook, Vol. 1, 7th ed. pg. 18.2Criteria for atopic dermatitisMajor criteriaAn itchy skin condition (plus 3 or more of the following)1. Onset below 2 years2. History of skin crease involvement (including cheeks in children under 10 years)3. History of generally dry skin4. History of other atopic diseases5. Visible flexural dermatitis.Atopic dermatitis could be established if 3 of the major and 3 of the 23 minor criteria are present.Contact dermatitis is unlikely in this age group.Seborrhic dermatitis - The seborrheic areas like scalp, nasolabial fold, retroauricular areas are affected.",
