          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Pemphigus vulgaris is characterized by cutaneous and mucosal blisters. On application of tangential pressure on normal skin results in formation of new bulla (Nikolsky sign) or if applied to pre-existing bulla results in the spread of bulla (bulla spread sign). Cutaneous lesions predominantly present on face, trunk, axillae, groins, and scalp. Ref: Illustrated Synopsis Of Dermatology & Sexually Transmitted Diseases By Khanna, 3rd edition, Page 64."
