          "id": "medmcqa-de73088e-3446-48d3-a6fa-fe5929150d8f",
          "text": "A 85-year-old female developed multiple blisters on trunk and thighs. Nikolsky's sign negative. The lesions came on and off. The most probable diagnosis is:",
