          "id": "medmcqa-f095be4b-dc91-475c-8fc6-22ed4519605a",
          "text": "Physical examination of a 14 year old boy demonstrates six coffee-colored skin macules up to 3 cm in diameter. No other skin lesions are noted, but a small mass lesion is felt in the subcutaneous tissues below two of the macules. These masses are most likely closely associated with which of the following structures?",
